runs.comm: short of a good length outside off, guides that one down to third man for a single
good length, in the channel outside off stump and it's left alone to the keeper
short outside off, was aiming at cover but ended up mistiming it to the bowler instead
there is a long-on in place, drives that one down to the fielder there for a single
shortish on the off, pushes that past point into the deep for a single
nicely played but there is protection in the deep, pitched up on middle and he's picked it wide of long-on, on the bounce, the fielder collects it and a single is all they'll manage
tossed up on middle, gets forward and drives it into the leg side for a single
flatter from Badree here, gets forward and turns it towards short fine for a single
flat on middle, rocks forward and defends it into the off side
short outside off and it's cut straight to short third man
shortish on middle, quicker through the air, comes down the track and punches it to extra cover
fullish on the pads and that's clipped past short fine for a single to keep strike
shortish on the off, gets on the back foot and jabs it to midwicket
Rampaul strikes early! Nicol had moved well across as he tried to clip that straightish delivery over short fine, missed and I reckon he was trapped in front of middle and leg
a bit of inswing there for Rampaul, goodish length, McCullum goes back to defend, gets an inside edge onto the pads as he tries to do that

thick inside edge and Narine misfields at short third man, pushed it fuller did Rampaul and McCullum's attempted drive through the leg side didn't work out as he planned, still he gets a boundary past short fine
shortish on the off, drops it in front of point and steals a quick single
beaten, good length and he gets it to nip away, drives that away from his body there and can't connect
flat on leg stump and McCullum looks to pull that square, but gets an inside edge onto the pads
quicker on middle, goes on straight, defended into the off side towards cover
mid-off inside the circle and McCullum comes down the track, takes it off a length and drills that down the ground for four
pushed it quicker on middle, skids after pitching, pushed away into the leg side for a single
gets across and turns that towards square leg
slower through the air this time, legspinner, pulls that straight to mid-on
pitched up on middle and it's driven straight back to the bowler
Guptill makes a bit of room there to smack that over extra cover, misses, a bit of frustration from Guptill there, has struggled to get going so far
connects well this time, short of a length and Guptill latches onto it, gets forward and pulls that smartly over midwicket
a bit of width and it's crunched hard towards mid-off but Russell gathers it easily and prevents the single
slower one bowled on middle, drags it towards midwicket for a quick single
short of a good length, punched towards extra cover and steals a quick single
the offspinner on middle and leg, tries to turn it away square, gets a leg-bye
shortish on the off, a bit of inward turn, gets on the back foot and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
short and he pulls it with the turn, too short there and he pulls that through square leg for a boundary
goodish length on middle, this seemed to me to be the carrom ball, rocked forward and he defended it into the off side
tossed up on middle, drives that through midwicket into the deep, by the time Pollard gets around to it, they have taken two
shortish on middle, gets on the back foot to turn it into the leg side for a single
short from him and it's pulled through square leg, a couple of runs as deep square leg cuts it off
slower one bowled outside off, pushed through point for a single
would have been a wide but Guptill reaches for it and cuts it down to deep point for a single
goodish length this time, McCullum shuffles across and defends that with a full face to the bowler
angling in towards middle, drives it down the ground to long-on for a single
short of a length outside off, cut away towards deep point for a single
Badree bowls that flat on leg stump, turns it away wide of midwicket for a single

McCullum's bowled! Badree continues to bowl flat and straight, McCullum came down the track, made a bit of room for himself simultaneously and tried to whack that through cover but played over it and missed, it shot straight on to strike middle
gives it some air this time, tossed up on middle, tickled towards square leg to get off the mark
the googly, turned in from outside off and took the outside edge as he defended inside the line, short third dived to his left to keep them to a single
Taylor paddles that really fine, fetched it from middle and off for a couple of runs
bowled quick and flat on the off stump, defended towards cover from the crease
Sammy slips in the slower one outside off and Guptill is beaten while trying to drive it through extra cover
third man is inside the circle and Guptill plays it smartly, short of a good length and he opens the face to guide that between point and short third
that slipped out of his hand, brings up the New Zealand 50 thanks to a wide
pitched on a length on the off, drives that down the ground to long-on for a single
angling in towards the off, pushes that wide of extra cover for a single
angling in towards middle, gets on the back foot and defends it to the bowler
New Zealand are slipping, short and wide and Guptill senses a chance but he can't keep it down, cuts that straight to point where Samuels takes it easily
shortish on leg stump, tries to turn it fine, gets a leg-bye
pushed it fuller outside off, was the googly, driven straight to extra cover
slightly short on the off, defends it towards extra cover off the back foot
the googly again, shortish, cuts it down to point and Taylor running at the danger end makes it in time, but had it been a direct hit Taylor was gone, run-out attempt, a close one
tossed up on middle this time, worked it wide of Pollard at midwicket for a single, Pollard dives to his right and releases quickly
tossed up on the off, driven down towards long-off for a single
short of a good length on the off, guided that one straight to point
pulled away, short of a length, picks it up from outside off and smacks it over midwicket for a boundary, nicely struck
pitched up, follows it and drops it in front of extra cover for a single
angling in towards middle, drives it down the ground to long-on for a single
full toss, a slow full toss outside off, drops it in front of point for a single
angling in towards off, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
round the wicket to the left-hander, quicker, punched through midwicket into the deep for a couple of runs
shortish on leg stump, played away to deep backward square leg for a single
got well across did Ross, and played it well in the end though there was a big lbw risk there, he plays that shot well though, gets across and swings it fine, past short fine, for a boundary
tickles that one towards short fine this time for a single
shortish outside off, chopped towards point, Badree throws needlessly at the non-striker's end and concedes an overthrow
bad ball from Gayle, a full toss on middle and Taylor dispatches that over the deep square leg boundary, easy pickings there and relieves a bit of the pressure, Badree's agony grows
round the wicket to the left-hander, on the off stump, defended towards point for a single
misdirected, was a wide but he's overstepped as well, so it's a no-ball, freehit coming
caught at long-off as Taylor reaches for a widish delivery and holes out in the deep, just the single though
shortish on leg, turned in towards Franklin and he swept it wide of short fine for a single
turns in from outside off, worked away into the on side, in the vacant square leg region for a well-run couple
Taylor gets across and drives that through midwicket for a single

superbly caught by Gayle, it was the carrom ball, spun in from outside off and Franklin tried to open the face, got a thick edge and Gayle reacted quick, snapping a sharp catch stretching to his right and taking it one-handed
short of a good length outside off, tapped towards point and he picks a single
short of a length outside off, Oram's off the mark by guiding that one down to third man for a single
nicely done by Taylor, on a good length, gets to it and steers that past the diving point to beat third man to the boundary
angling in towards middle, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
goodish length, gets front and across and drives it down to long-on for a single
good length outside off, stabs it wide of extra cover for a single
pushed it full on the off and that was driven past the diving bowler to long-off for a single
goodish length on the off, gets front and across and drives it back to the bowler
shortish on the off, pulls it through square leg into the deep for a couple more runs
slower one, pushed it towards Gayle at extra cover, Taylor picked a single and took another one on the overthrow as Gayle missed at the non-striker's end
yorkerish outside off and it's dug out towards point for a single
slower one bowled on a length on the off and Oram defends it back to the bowler, and Pollard gives the batsman a stare
short of a good length, Taylor tries to chop it towards point, knocks it away just into the off side, no single on offer
Taylor slogs and slogs well, picked it up from a length outside off and heaved it over the deep midwicket boundary, went the distance

four more, Andre Russell was caught in two minds about what to do there, was in the air for a while and Russell initially thought of going for a catch but it wasn't on, Taylor flicked it beautifully towards deep square leg and Russell dived forward, only for the ball to bounce over him
dragged through square leg this time for just a single
round the wicket to Oram and he chips it through midwicket for a single
bad ball, full toss on leg stump and he's lucky that's not been smacked for another boundary, flicked away through square leg for a couple more in the deep
floating it on leg and middle, drives that straight to extra cover
shortish on leg stump, an offspinner, punched through midwicket into an open gap that fetches them two runs
the offspinner, shortish outside off, cut down straight to point, dot ball

Narine gets him with the carrom ball, that one spun in and Oram simply didn't pick it. Lands on middle and turns towards leg, Oram plants his foot forward and is rapped on the pads, the decision the umpire had to make was whether that was missing leg. He didn't think so, Oram did, but what Oram thinks doesn't matter. He has to go
gets well across does Nathan, struck on the pads as he tries to sweep, outside the line, misses
beaten by the one that goes the other way, again, short of a good length and it turns away and just goes past the outside edge, good stuff from Narine
pitched on a good length outside off, slapped towards deep point for a single
goodish length, pushed gently towards extra cover for a single
nicely driven on the up and that's been played wide of long-off for a couple of runs
pitched on a length and that's been crunched down to long-off for a single
two more, full outside off and that's been steered behind point, Russell runs to his right, slides and keeps them down to a couple
full toss but not a costly one, pulls it towards deep midwicket for a single to keep strike
Nathan plays the reverse-sweep and plays it straight to Gayle at point, just the single
shortish on the off, goes on straight, Taylor reaches his half-century with a whip to square leg for a single
Nathan holes out, Narine picks up his third, the pressure grows on New Zealand, he had to go for it and found deep midwicket, couldn't connect as well and got more height than distance
ooh, a dot ball, the carrom ball, got across and dropped it into the leg side, thought of the single but it just wasn't there
the carrom ball again, turned away, short outside off, Taylor moved away to cut and missed, another dot, what a superb over this
Taylor opts to take the single, drops it towards point to keep strike, Narine ends a potentially match-winning spell
fires it quick but it's down the leg side, Ramdin keeps well and takes off the bails but Taylor's in, a wide
yorker length and superbly done by Marlon., Taylor can only push it back to the bowler, applause from Gayle
misfield by Narine, he's been sloppy in the field today though very good with the ball, clips it towards short fine, he concedes an extra run, two in all
low full toss and it's chipped towards Pollard at long-on for two more, Taylor makes it back in time

plays the scoop and it goes all the way, it's not his favourite shot but he pulls it off superbly, full toss on the pads, bowled at 127kmph and he used the pace to scoop it over the fine-leg boundary for six, what a shot
ooh fired it quick on middle, got an inside edge onto the pads, just the single, 2 in 1 now
full toss and it's flicked towards deep square leg, it's Super Over folks, they pick a single and Bracewell is run out on the second run, a direct hit from the deep
